    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <note type="editorial" resp="#ww" place="top">W. W. | Answ'd Oct 3/84.</note>
            <opener> 
                <dateline>   
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey</name>
                    <date when="1884-09-29" rend="right">September 29 '84<ptr target="nyp.00536_n1"
                        /></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Enclosed a little piece the whole idea of which I got from you&#8212;as you see. It
                is in the <hi rend= "italic">Critic</hi> of Sept. 27<ptr target="nyp.00536_n2"/>&#8212;Dry and warm and
                often oppressive weather here&#8212;a long spell&#8212;My lameness seems permanent
                like&#8212;I have promised to write a War Hospital Article for <hi rend="italic">Century</hi> to supplement
                their forthcoming swell [of] war narratives by Grant &#38; the rest.<ptr
                    target="nyp.00536_n3"/></p>
            <p>William, I wonder if you or Charles Eldridge couldn't help me to something there from
                the Medical Bureau&#8212;summaries, or statistics or any information&#8212;who do
                you know in the Surgeon Gen[eral]'s office?<ptr target="nyp.00536_n4"/></p>

            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
